shingle
Homonym Number: 1
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a piece of split (now also sawn) wood, usually rectangular used for roofing is general English (OED from 1200) but OED quotations (esp. in combinations) seem to have a provincial, and later a `colonial' flavour, although the sense does not occur in EDD. Certainly in early NZ, shingles were perhaps the commonest roofing material. British observers in the 19th century often feel obliged to explain the term. e.g.
